I was in the area to have lunch with a colleague and he suggested we go here. When I saw the place I thought to myself there must be something nicer in the area but I was pleasantly surprised once I stepped inside. It has a generations of family have grown up going there kind of vibe. The place isn't aesthetically pleasing but the wait was pretty short and the food was so good. We both had the bacon egg and cheese deluxe with the iced tea. It was so good that I regretted not taking pictures before I started to eat. Overall I recommend this location but be prepared for the following: no avocadoes...I wanted to add to the burger but they don't have any which surprised me and even more important: CASH ONLY! I wish I would have been told or for there to be a sign on the way in. I found this out after giving the waitress my credit card to pay. Luckily I had $28 cash on me....enough to cover the $24 meal for two plus tip.
